  "body": "#üêû Bug Report\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nIn current master, if you have a direct-type wallet and try to import using accounts-v2 import, something like the following happens:\r\nAttempt 1) Try the correct password <--- All goes well\r\nAttempt 2) Try an incorrect password and the program keeps looping until you provide a good password. <--- The first (incorrect) password becomes the new password after the new keystore is written.\r\nAttempt 3) The previously incorrect password now works.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\t\tenc, password, err = askUntilPasswordConfirms(decryptor, keystoreFile)\r\n\t\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\t\treturn errors.Wrap(err, \"could not confirm password via prompt\")\r\n\t\t}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe password variable that is returned by askUntilPasswordConfirms() is ignored and the old (wrong) password remains.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\nUnsure\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nSee above\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\nAs described above.\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\nWindows 10 as well as a docker container within an Ubuntu VM.\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n3147a5ee01342788d3b1d1f8c52a85ecacc80ded\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\nNo\r\n\r\n",
